## Project Structure
This workspace contains:
- `/testing/` - SDET learning materials, phase documents, resumes, prompts
- `/hybrid_agent/` - Project 2 (MCP Hybrid Memory Agent)
- `/kngraphs/` - Knowledge graph learning materials
- `/vector_dbs/` - Vector DB learning materials

## Learning Phases (Strict Sequence)
1. **Phase A** - Foundations (SDLC, STLC, system flows, Playwright theory, API theory, Git, debugging)
2. **Phase B** - Build SDLC Simulator App (Project 1)
3. **Phase C** - Build Automation Framework (Project 3)
4. **Phase D** - Interview Mastery (resume, narratives, mock interviews)

## Phase Gate Rules
- **A → B**: User must demonstrate understanding of all Phase A concepts
- **B → C**: App must be complete, documented, and user understands architecture
- **C → D**: Framework must work, CI/CD green, user can explain architecture

## Code Generation Rules
- **Phase A**: NO CODE - concepts only
- **Phase B**: Minimal, testable, deterministic code only
- **Phase C**: Clean framework architecture, no over-engineering
- Always show architecture/design BEFORE code
- Use known tools only (Playwright, Python, Pytest, GitHub Actions)
- No hallucinated libraries

## File Organization Rules
- Phase documents in `/testing/` folder
- Project code in dedicated folders (created during phases)
- Keep learning materials separate from implementation
- Document everything that will go on resume

